<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="541" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,258,427]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,258,283]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The female of the new species is most similar to that of the Central Asian 
<taxonomicName authority="Li &amp; Yang, 1994" authorityName="Li &amp; Yang" authorityYear="1994" class="Insecta" family="Sphecidae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vetuberosa">
<emphasis box="[1142,1297,259,283]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">A. vetuberosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Li" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" refString="Li, Q., Li, Ji. &amp; Yang, J. (1994) A classification study on Ammophila Kirby from Shandong with the description of a new species (Hymenoptera: Sphecidae). Journal of Shandong Agricultural University, 25, 289 - 292. [in Chinese]" type="journal article" year="1994">
Li &amp; Yang, 
<quantity box="[151,207,295,319]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.06476" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" unit="in" value="1994.0">1994</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in having an apical tooth on the posterior surface of the forecoxa, but differs in having denser appressed silvery setae of the entire body, all red metasoma, and shiny sculpture of the mesoscutum (in 
<taxonomicName box="[1236,1392,331,355]" class="Insecta" family="Sphecidae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vetuberosa">
<emphasis box="[1236,1392,331,355]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">A. vetuberosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the appressed silvery setae of the body are less dense, T 
<number box="[728,740,366,391]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="5.0">5</number>
–T 
<number box="[774,787,366,391]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="6.0">6</number>
and S 
<number box="[855,868,366,391]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="5.0">5</number>
–S 
<number box="[899,913,366,391]" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" value="6.0">6</number>
of metasoma are black, and the mesoscutum is mat). The male of 
<taxonomicName box="[358,481,403,426]" class="Insecta" family="Sphecidae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pevtsovi">
<emphasis box="[358,481,403,426]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="541">A. pevtsovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242034/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="541" targetBox="[163,1428,515,1878]" targetPageId="4">
