Li &amp; Yang
</taxonomicName>
; 14. Specimen, female, lateral view, labels; 15. Specimen, male, lateral view, labels; 16. Female clypeus.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="542" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="542">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,450,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="542">Description. Female.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[614,700,152,176]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="5" pageNumber="542" unit="mm" value="17.0">17 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[716,776,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="542">Head</emphasis>
. Mandible dark brown. Median lobe of clypeus slightly elongate; black with brown ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[668,756,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 16. 11 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1911,1934]" captionTargetBox="[163,1428,515,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,510,1890]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 16. 11 – 13. Ammophila pevtsovi Danilov sp. nov.; 11. Holotype: specimen, lateral view, labels; 12. Clypeus; 13. Mesosoma, dorsal view; 14 – 16. Ammophila vetuberosa Li &amp; Yang; 14. Specimen, female, lateral view, labels; 15. Specimen, male, lateral view, labels; 16. Female clypeus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242034/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="542">
Fig. 
<number box="[725,756,188,212]" pageId="5" pageNumber="542" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Clypeus (except ventral margin), face, gena and occiput covered with dense appressed silvery setae. Vertex covered with sparse appressed silvery setae. Erect setae of head white only. Flagellomeres black. 
<taxonomicName box="[546,666,261,284]" class="Crustacea" family="Crustacea" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea" pageId="5" pageNumber="542" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[546,666,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="542">Mesosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Black; covered with very dense appressed silvery setae, except mesoscutal disk and propodeal enclosure (which are glabrous and shiny). Erect setae white. Mesoscutum shine (
<figureCitation box="[159,244,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 16. 11 – 13" captionStartId="4.[151,263,1911,1934]" captionTargetBox="[163,1428,515,1878]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,510,1890]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 16. 11 – 13. Ammophila pevtsovi Danilov sp. nov.; 11. Holotype: specimen, lateral view, labels; 12. Clypeus; 13. Mesosoma, dorsal view; 14 – 16. Ammophila vetuberosa Li &amp; Yang; 14. Specimen, female, lateral view, labels; 15. Specimen, male, lateral view, labels; 16. Female clypeus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242034/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="542">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,244,332,356]" pageId="5" pageNumber="542" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
). Propodeal enclosure glabrous, obliquely striate. Tegula yellowish. 
<emphasis box="[1029,1097,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="542">Wings</emphasis>
. Hyaline with slightly darker apical part; wing venation light brown; costal vein dark brown. Submarginal cell III petiolate. 
<emphasis box="[1291,1344,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="542">Legs</emphasis>
. Black, pruinose; tarsus brown. Forecoxal apex with tooth. 
<emphasis box="[727,843,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="542">Metasoma</emphasis>
. All red.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
